import { Container, Row, Image, Col, Card, Button } from 'react-bootstrap';
import React from 'react'

class Login extends React.Component {
    render() {
        return (
            <Container className='h-100 align-middle'>
                <Row className='h-100'>
                    <Col className='m-auto img_login p-0'>
                        <Image className='w-100  ' src="https://colorlib.com/etc/lf/Login_v18/images/bg-01.jpg" rounded></Image>
                    </Col>
                    <Col className='m-auto p-0'>
                        <Card className='m-auto'>
                            <Card.Body>
                                <Card.Title>Đăng nhập</Card.Title>
                                <Card.Subtitle className="mb-2 text-muted">Welcome back, Vui lòng </Card.Subtitle>
                                <Card.Text>
                                    Some quick example text to build on the card title and make up the bulk of
                                    the card's content.
    </Card.Text>
                                <Card.Link href="#">Card Link</Card.Link>
                                <Card.Link href="#">Another Link</Card.Link>
                            </Card.Body>
                        </Card>
                    </Col>
                </Row>
            </Container>
        )
    }
}
export default Login;
